@(1-8=c2431.A.1) …… protective deity ……. @wRN{Amar-@wDN{Suena}} …… his heart. He who …… the temple with an axe ……. @wRN{Amar-@wDN{Suena}} …… the @fsux{abzu} shrine. …… built with gold, and decorated with lapis lazuli. He applied himself to building the temple; King @wRN{Amar-@wDN{Suena}} applied himself to building the temple. The people turned against the king, and the foreign countries …….

@(9-25=c2431.A.9) In the first year the temple remained in ruins, and he did not restore it. @wRN{Amar-@wDN{Suena}} …… the divine powers of kingship. In the second year it remained in ruins, and he did not restore it. @wRN{Amar-@wDN{Suena}} …… his royal garments for mourning clothes. In the third year it remained in ruins, and he did not restore it. @wRN{Amar-@wDN{Suena}} could not interpret (?) the temple's ominous sign among (?) the birch trees. In the fourth year it remained in ruins, and he did not restore it. Although he had been advised (?) by a sage, he could not realise the plans of the temple. In the fifth year it remained in ruins, and he did not restore it. The @fsux{abzu} shrine has been …… by force. In the sixth year it remained in ruins, and he did not restore it. He was searching for the divine plan of the temple, but could not find it. In the seventh year it remained in ruins, and he did not restore it. @wDN{Enki} spoke to him about the temple, the temple that did not exist. In the eighth year, he applied himself to building the temple. By the ninth year, King @wRN{Amar-@wDN{Suena}} built the @wTN{E-uduna} of the wise lord (?) like …….

